                <head>181. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>According to the records of the United States Delegation, Secretary of State
                        <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName> met with <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MAD1"
                        >MacArthur</persName> at his villa at 8 a.m. Other than a notation on the
                    delegation order of the day, no record has been found of this meeting. (<gloss
                        target="#t_USDel1">USDEL</gloss> OD–2a (1st revision), July 18; Department
                    of State, Conference Files: Lot 63 D 123, CF 520)</p>
                <p>Following this meeting, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>, and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MAD1">MacArthur</persName> were joined by <persName
                        corresp="#p_BRR1">Bowie</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_MCCW1"
                        >McCardle</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_PH1">Phleger</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_BCEC1">Bohlen</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_TLE1"
                        >Thompson</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_BJD1">Beam</persName> for a
                    small staff meeting, during which an intelligence briefing was given and the
                    United States, foreign, and Soviet press reactions were analyzed. Other than a
                    notation on the delegation order of the day (<gloss target="#t_USDel1"
                        >USDEL</gloss> OD–2a (1st revision)) and another draft of the order of the
                    day (SUM OD–1, July 18), no record of this staff meeting has been found. (<hi
                        rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> CF 520 and CF 513, respectively)</p>
            </div>
